{{Infobox ancient site|type = {{ill|Round Kofun|ja|円墳|1=Round Kofun|1=Round Kofun|12=draft|12=draft}} | name = Taniguchi-yama Kofun | image = [[File:Yaguchiyama Kofun.jpg|280px]] | caption = View from the south | alternate_name = | Cluster = | location = {{ill|Utsunomiya|ja|宇都宮市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Tochigi Prefecture|ja|栃木県|12=draft|12=draft}}, Nagaokachō 1258-4{{sfn|塙|2008|p=112}} | coordinates = {{Coord|36|35|51.2|N|139|53|34.3|E|region:JP-09_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} | type = {{ill|Round barrow|ja|円墳|1=Round Kofun|1=Round Kofun|12=draft|12=draft}}{{sfn|塙|2008|p=112}} | area = Diameter ~29 m × Height 3.6 m{{sfn|塙|2008|p=112}}{{sfn|梁木・今平|1995|p=27}} | burial = {{ill|Yokoana-style stone chamber|ja|横穴式石室|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=横穴式石室|4=zh|5=橫穴式石室|6=ko|7=굴식 돌방무덤|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=横穴式石室|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=横穴式石室|4=zh|5=橫穴式石室|6=ko|7=굴식 돌방무덤|4=zh|5=橫穴式石室|6=ko|7=굴식 돌방무덤|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|12=draft|12=draft}}{{sfn|塙|2008|p=112}} | burial goods = Human remains, iron swords, iron arrowheads, earrings, glass beads, horse trappings<ref name="ku">{{Cite web|ja|url=https://www.city.utsunomiya.tochigi.jp/_res/projects/default_project/_page_/001/014/535/08.pdf|title=谷口山古墳|author=Yamada Takashi|work=Utsunomiya Monthly, February 1993|date=1993-02|publisher=Utsunomiya City|accessdate=2021-05-31}}</ref> | Satellite Barrows = | built = Late 6th century{{sfn|塙|2008|p=112}} | Interred_individual = | Mausoleum = | Heritage designation1 = Utsunomiya City Historic Site<ref name="ku"/> | designation1 = | Archeological Site ID = | notes = | map = Japan Tochigi | map = | type = Round barrow | map_dot_label = | map_dot_label = }} [[File:Yaguchiyama Kofun tomb entrance.jpg|thumb|Entrance to the stone chamber]] '''Taniguchi-yama Kofun''' (谷口山古墳{{sfn|梁木・今平|1995|p=21}}{{sfn|塙|2008|p=112}}) is a {{ill|Round barrow|ja|円墳|1=Round Kofun|1=Round Kofun|12=draft|12=draft}} located in {{ill|Utsunomiya|ja|宇都宮市|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Tochigi Prefecture|ja|栃木県|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Overview == The Taniguchi-yama Kofun is estimated to have a diameter of approximately 29 meters and a height of 3.6 meters{{sfn|塙|2008|p=112}}. A surrounding moat, about 0.5–1.1 meters wide and 0.6 meters deep, has been identified{{sfn|梁木・今平|1995|p=27}}. The tumulus was significantly leveled during the construction of a parking lot where it was discovered<ref name="ku"/>.
The site features a {{ill|Yokoana-style stone chamber|ja|横穴式石室|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=横穴式石室|4=zh|5=橫穴式石室|6=ko|7=굴식 돌방무덤|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=横穴式石室|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=横穴式石室|4=zh|5=橫穴式石室|6=ko|7=굴식 돌방무덤|4=zh|5=橫穴式石室|6=ko|7=굴식 돌방무덤|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|12=draft|12=draft}} that was intact at the time of discovery. The chamber contained human remains and burial goods, maintaining their original burial configuration, making this tomb a valuable archaeological find{{sfn|塙|2008|p=112}}. As of 2021, the stone chamber is open to the public in its excavated state{{sfn|塙|2008|pp=112-113}}.
burial goods recovered from the site include: * Human remains of three individuals * Three iron swords * Three iron arrowheads * Three earrings * 147 glass beads * One piece of horse trappings (part of a bit)
These findings suggest the tomb was constructed in the late {{ill|Kofun period|ja|古墳時代|12=draft|12=draft}}, during the latter half of the 6th century.
== Discovery and Excavation == The tomb was discovered in late February 1991 during the construction of a parking lot for the Immanuel Utsunomiya Christian Church{{sfn|梁木・今平|1995|p=23}}. Upon its discovery, the Utsunomiya City Board of Education's Cultural Division initiated a survey on February 25{{sfn|梁木・今平|1995|p=23}}. Excavation work began on April 12 and concluded on July 8, with a public site explanation held on June 1{{sfn|梁木・今平|1995|p=23}}.
The site's landowner expressed deep admiration for the tomb's significance, contributing to its preservation rather than redevelopment<ref name="ku"/>. The site's excellent condition and the intact burial chamber led to its Historic Site as a Utsunomiya City designation1 (Historic Site) on November 27, 1991<ref name="ku"/>{{sfn|梁木・今平|1995|loc=序}}.
== Surrounding Environment == The Taniguchi-yama Kofun is situated in the southern area of the {{ill|Utsunomiya Hills|ja|宇都宮丘陵|12=draft|12=draft}}, along the western banks of the {{ill|Tagawa River (Tone River System)|ja|田川|12=draft|12=draft}} near {{ill|Tomatsuriyama|ja|戸祭山|12=draft|12=draft}}. The region contains numerous other ancient tombs and archaeological sites, including the {{ill|Tomatsuri Ōtsuka Kofun|ja|戸祭大塚古墳|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Kitayama Kofun Cluster|ja|北山古墳群|12=draft|12=draft}}, {{ill|Kawarazuka Kofun Cluster|ja|瓦塚古墳群|12=draft|12=draft}}, and {{ill|Nagaoka Hyakuana Kofun|ja|長岡百穴古墳|1=Nagaoka Hundred Caves|12=draft|12=draft}}, as well as {{ill|Nara period|ja|奈良時代|12=draft|12=draft}} ruins such as the {{ill|Suidōyama Tile Kiln Site|ja|水道山瓦窯跡|12=draft|12=draft}}. These sites are connected by the {{ill|Toyosato Mahoroba Road|ja|豊郷まほろばの道|12=draft|12=draft}}.
== Access == ; By Bus * From {{ill|Utsunomiya Station|ja|宇都宮駅|12=draft|12=draft}} (JR West Exit): ** Take the {{ill|Kantō Bus|ja|関東自動車|12=draft|12=draft}} to Teikyo University/Utsunomiya Museum of Art, or the New Fujimi line (15 minutes); alight at "Midori-ga-Oka Entrance," 5 minutes on foot. Alternatively, take the Tamanyu or Utsunomiya Green Town line to "Toyosato Central Elementary School" (15 minutes) and walk for 15 minutes.
; By Car * From National Route 119 (Utsunomiya Ring Road): ** Proceed north from Nagaokamachi Intersection (5 minutes), or west from the Sekibori-cho North Intersection on the {{ill|Nagaoka Road|ja|長岡街道|12=draft|12=draft}} (1 minute).
