The site's landowner expressed deep admiration for the tomb's significance, contributing to its preservation rather than redevelopment<ref name="ku"/>. The site's excellent condition and the intact burial chamber led to its Historic Site as a Utsunomiya City designation1 (Historic Site) on November 27, 1991<ref name="ku"/>{{sfn|梁木・今平|1995|loc=序}}.
== Surrounding Environment == The Taniguchi-yama Kofun is situated in the southern area of the {{ill|Utsunomiya Hills|ja|宇都宮丘陵|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Utsunomiya Hills|qq=}}, along the western banks of the {{ill|Tagawa River (Tone River System)|ja|田川|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tagawa River (Tone River System)|qq=}} near {{ill|Tomatsuriyama|ja|戸祭山|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tomatsuriyama|qq=}}. The region contains numerous other ancient tombs and archaeological sites, including the {{ill|Tomatsuri Ōtsuka Kofun|ja|戸祭大塚古墳|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Tomatsuri Ōtsuka Kofun|qq=}}, {{ill|Kitayama Kofun Cluster|ja|北山古墳群|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kitayama Kofun Cluster|qq=}}, {{ill|Kawarazuka Kofun Group|lt=Kawarazuka Kofun Group|lt=Kawarazuka Kofun Cluster|ja|瓦塚古墳群|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kawarazuka Kofun Cluster|qq=}}, and {{ill|Nagaoka Hyakuana Kofun|ja|長岡百穴古墳|1=Nagaoka Hundred Caves|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagaoka Hyakuana Kofun|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagaoka Hundred Caves|qq=}}, as well as [[:en:Nara period|Nara period]] ruins such as the {{ill|Suidōyama Tile Kiln Site|ja|水道山瓦窯跡|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Suidōyama Tile Kiln Site|qq=}}. These sites are connected by the {{ill|Toyosato Mahoroba Road|ja|豊郷まほろばの道|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Toyosato Mahoroba Road|qq=}}.
== Access == ; By Bus * From [[:en:Utsunomiya Station|Utsunomiya Station]] (JR West Exit): ** Take the {{ill|Kantō Bus|ja|関東自動車|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kantō Bus|qq=}} to Teikyo University/Utsunomiya Museum of Art, or the New Fujimi line (15 minutes); alight at "Midori-ga-Oka Entrance," 5 minutes on foot. Alternatively, take the Tamanyu or Utsunomiya Green Town line to "Toyosato Central Elementary School" (15 minutes) and walk for 15 minutes.
; By Car * From National Route 119 (Utsunomiya Ring Road): ** Proceed north from Nagaokamachi Intersection (5 minutes), or west from the Sekibori-cho North Intersection on the {{ill|Nagaoka Road|ja|長岡街道|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Nagaoka Road|qq=}} (1 minute).
